x4freetext: 25 MeV Electron LINAC based pulsed
neutron source at Centro Atomico Bariloche, operated
at a repetition rate of 50 Hz and 12 uA average
current.
A lead target and a 4 cm slab shaped polyethylene
moderator were employed to obtain a thermal neutron
spectrum.
The sample was placed at about 360 cm from the neutron
source in a separate room shielded by 100 cm thick
concrete wall.
flight path =(827.2+-0.5)cm.
The sample-in sample-out method was used.
Standard normalized transmission measurement.
In all the cases, the experimental data were
normalized in the free atom region to the cross
section value of each molecule unit (S.F.Mughabghab,
M.Divadeenam, Neutron Cross Section, Academic Press,
The detector bank consisted of seven 3He
proportional counters (10 atm filling pressure,
15.24 cm active length, 2.54 cm diameter), placed at
(827.2 +- 0.5) cm from the thermal neutron source,
as determined by the use of well known neutron
absorption resonances.
Statistical error
Uncertainty in the temperature
Data were received from Dr. Florencia Cantargi
Entry approved by Dr. Florencia Cantargi

On. BIB: Formal corrections only
Commercial toluene with purity of 99.5%, was used in
the measurements. A coin shaped aluminum sample holder
of (4.000 +- 0.002) cm inner diameter and
(0.214 +- 0.002) cm inner thickness sealed with an
indium ring was used for the total cross sections
determination.
